    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "mn98:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:2.1",
          "pli": "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā brāhmaṇamahāsālā icchānaṅgale paṭivasanti, seyyathidaṃ—",
          "en": "Now at that time several very well-known well-to-do brahmins were residing in Icchānaṅgala. They included "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:2.2",
          "pli": "caṅkī brāhmaṇo, tārukkho brāhmaṇo, pokkharasāti brāhmaṇo, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo, todeyyo brāhmaṇo, aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā brāhmaṇamahāsālā. ",
          "en": "the brahmins Caṅkī, Tārukkha, Pokkharasāti, Jāṇussoṇi, Todeyya, and others. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho vāseṭṭhabhāradvājānaṃ māṇavānaṃ jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamantānaṃ anuvicarantānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: ",
          "en": "Then as the brahmin students Vāseṭṭha and Bhāradvāja were going for a walk they began to discussion the question of "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.2",
          "pli": "“kathaṃ, bho, brāhmaṇo hotī”ti? ",
          "en": "how one is a brahmin. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.3",
          "pli": "Bhāradvājo māṇavo evamāha: ",
          "en": "Bhāradvāja said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.4",
          "pli": "“yato kho, bho, ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena—",
          "en": "“When you’re well born on both your mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.5",
          "pli": "ettāvatā kho, bho, brāhmaṇo hotī”ti. ",
          "en": "then you’re a brahmin.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.6",
          "pli": "Vāseṭṭho māṇavo evamāha: ",
          "en": "Vāseṭṭha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.7",
          "pli": "“yato kho, bho, sīlavā ca hoti vattasampanno ca—",
          "en": "“When you’re ethical and accomplished in doing your duties—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:3.8",
          "pli": "ettāvatā kho, bho, brāhmaṇo hotī”ti. ",
          "en": "then you’re a brahmin.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:4.1",
          "pli": "Neva kho asakkhi bhāradvājo māṇavo vāseṭṭhaṃ māṇavaṃ saññāpetuṃ, na pana asakkhi vāseṭṭho māṇavo bhāradvājaṃ māṇavaṃ saññāpetuṃ. ",
          "en": "But neither was able to persuade the other. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho vāseṭṭho māṇavo bhāradvājaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi: ",
          "en": "So Vāseṭṭha said to Bhāradvāja, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.2",
          "pli": "“ayaṃ kho, bho bhāradvāja, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe. ",
          "en": "“Master Bhāradvāja, the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—is staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.3",
          "pli": "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: ",
          "en": "He has this good reputation: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.4",
          "pli": "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. ",
          "en": "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.5",
          "pli": "Āyāma, bho bhāradvāja, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ etamatthaṃ pucchissāma. ",
          "en": "Come, let’s go to see him and ask him about this matter. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.6",
          "pli": "Yathā no samaṇo gotamo byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti. ",
          "en": "As he answers, so we’ll remember it.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:5.7",
          "pli": "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho bhāradvājo māṇavo vāseṭṭhassa māṇavassa paccassosi. ",
          "en": "“Yes, sir,” replied Bhāradvāja. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:6.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho vāseṭṭhabhāradvājā māṇavā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. ",
          "en": "So they went to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:6.2",
          "pli": "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. ",
          "en": "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:6.3",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vāseṭṭho māṇavo bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: ",
          "en": "and Vāseṭṭha addressed the Buddha in verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.1",
          "pli": "“Anuññātapaṭiññātā, ",
          "en": "“We’re both authorized masters "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.2",
          "pli": "tevijjā mayamasmubho; ",
          "en": "of the three Vedas. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.3",
          "pli": "Ahaṃ pokkharasātissa, ",
          "en": "I’m a student of Pokkharasāti, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.4",
          "pli": "tārukkhassāyaṃ māṇavo. ",
          "en": "and he of Tārukkha. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.5",
          "pli": "Tevijjānaṃ yadakkhātaṃ, ",
          "en": "We’re fully qualified "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.6",
          "pli": "tatra kevalinosmase; ",
          "en": "in all the Vedic experts teach. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.7",
          "pli": "Padakasmā veyyākaraṇā, ",
          "en": "As philologists and grammarians, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.8",
          "pli": "jappe ācariyasādisā; ",
          "en": "we match our teachers in recitation. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.9",
          "pli": "Tesaṃ no jātivādasmiṃ, ",
          "en": "We have a dispute "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.10",
          "pli": "vivādo atthi gotama. ",
          "en": "regarding the question of ancestry. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.11",
          "pli": "Jātiyā brāhmaṇo hoti, ",
          "en": "For Bhāradvāja says that "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.12",
          "pli": "bhāradvājo iti bhāsati; ",
          "en": "one is a brahmin due to birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.13",
          "pli": "Ahañca kammunā brūmi, ",
          "en": "but I declare it’s because of one’s actions. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.14",
          "pli": "evaṃ jānāhi cakkhuma. ",
          "en": "Oh seer, know this as our debate. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.15",
          "pli": "Te na sakkoma ñāpetuṃ, ",
          "en": "Since neither of us was able "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.16",
          "pli": "aññamaññaṃ mayaṃ ubho; ",
          "en": "to convince the other, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.17",
          "pli": "Bhavantaṃ puṭṭhumāgamā, ",
          "en": "we’ve come to ask you, sir, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.18",
          "pli": "sambuddhaṃ iti vissutaṃ. ",
          "en": "so renowned as the awakened one. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.19",
          "pli": "Candaṃ yathā khayātītaṃ, ",
          "en": "As people honor with joined palms "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.20",
          "pli": "pecca pañjalikā janā; ",
          "en": "the moon on the cusp of waxing, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.21",
          "pli": "Vandamānā namassanti, ",
          "en": "bowing, they revere "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.22",
          "pli": "lokasmiṃ gotamaṃ. ",
          "en": "Gotama in the world. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.23",
          "pli": "Cakkhuṃ loke samuppannaṃ, ",
          "en": "We ask this of Gotama, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.24",
          "pli": "mayaṃ pucchāma gotamaṃ; ",
          "en": "the eye arisen in the world: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.25",
          "pli": "Jātiyā brāhmaṇo hoti, ",
          "en": "is one a brahmin due to birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.26",
          "pli": "udāhu bhavati kammunā; ",
          "en": "or else because of actions? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.27",
          "pli": "Ajānataṃ no pabrūhi, ",
          "en": "We don’t know, please tell us, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:7.28",
          "pli": "yathā jānemu brāhmaṇan”ti. ",
          "en": "so that we can know a brahmin.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.1",
          "pli": "“Tesaṃ vo ahaṃ byakkhissaṃ, (vāseṭṭhāti bhagavā) ",
          "en": "“I shall explain to you,” said the Buddha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.2",
          "pli": "Anupubbaṃ yathātathaṃ; ",
          "en": "“accurately and in sequence, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.3",
          "pli": "Jātivibhaṅgaṃ pāṇānaṃ, ",
          "en": "the taxonomy of living creatures, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.4",
          "pli": "Aññamaññāhi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.5",
          "pli": "Tiṇarukkhepi jānātha, ",
          "en": "Know the grass and trees, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.6",
          "pli": "na cāpi paṭijānare; ",
          "en": "though they lack self-awareness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.7",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ, ",
          "en": "They’re defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.8",
          "pli": "aññamaññā hi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.9",
          "pli": "Tato kīṭe paṭaṅge ca, ",
          "en": "Next there are bugs and moths, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.10",
          "pli": "yāva kunthakipillike; ",
          "en": "and so on, to ants and termites. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.11",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ, ",
          "en": "They’re defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.12",
          "pli": "aññamaññā hi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.13",
          "pli": "Catuppadepi jānātha, ",
          "en": "Know the quadrupeds, too, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.14",
          "pli": "khuddake ca mahallake; ",
          "en": "both small and large. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.15",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ, ",
          "en": "They’re defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.16",
          "pli": "aññamaññā hi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.17",
          "pli": "Pādudarepi jānātha, ",
          "en": "Know, too, the long-backed snakes, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.18",
          "pli": "urage dīghapiṭṭhike; ",
          "en": "crawling on their bellies. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.19",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ, ",
          "en": "They’re defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.20",
          "pli": "aññamaññā hi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.21",
          "pli": "Tato macchepi jānātha, ",
          "en": "Next know the fish, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.22",
          "pli": "udake vārigocare; ",
          "en": "whose habitat is the water. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.23",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ, ",
          "en": "They’re defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.24",
          "pli": "aññamaññā hi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.25",
          "pli": "Tato pakkhīpi jānātha, ",
          "en": "Next know the birds, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.26",
          "pli": "pattayāne vihaṅgame; ",
          "en": "flying with wings as chariots. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.27",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ, ",
          "en": "They’re defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:8.28",
          "pli": "aññamaññā hi jātiyo. ",
          "en": "for species are indeed diverse. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.1",
          "pli": "Yathā etāsu jātīsu, ",
          "en": "While the differences between these species "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.2",
          "pli": "liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ puthu; ",
          "en": "are defined by their birth, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.3",
          "pli": "Evaṃ natthi manussesu, ",
          "en": "the differences between humans "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.4",
          "pli": "liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ puthu. ",
          "en": "are not defined by their birth. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.5",
          "pli": "Na kesehi na sīsehi, ",
          "en": "Not by hair nor by head, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.6",
          "pli": "na kaṇṇehi na akkhīhi; ",
          "en": "not by ear nor by eye, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.7",
          "pli": "Na mukhena na nāsāya, ",
          "en": "not by mouth nor by nose, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.8",
          "pli": "na oṭṭhehi bhamūhi vā. ",
          "en": "not by lips nor by eyebrow, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.9",
          "pli": "Na gīvāya na aṃsehi, ",
          "en": "not by shoulder nor by neck, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.10",
          "pli": "na udarena na piṭṭhiyā; ",
          "en": "not by belly nor by back, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.11",
          "pli": "Na soṇiyā na urasā, ",
          "en": "not by buttocks nor by breast, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.12",
          "pli": "na sambādhe na methune. ",
          "en": "not by genitals nor by groin, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.13",
          "pli": "Na hatthehi na pādehi, ",
          "en": "not by hands nor by feet, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.14",
          "pli": "naṅgulīhi nakhehi vā; ",
          "en": "not by fingers nor by nails, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.15",
          "pli": "Na jaṅghāhi na ūrūhi, ",
          "en": "not by knees nor by thighs, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.16",
          "pli": "na vaṇṇena sarena vā; ",
          "en": "not by color nor by voice: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.17",
          "pli": "Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ neva, ",
          "en": "none of these are defined by birth "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.18",
          "pli": "yathā aññāsu jātisu. ",
          "en": "as it is for other species. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.19",
          "pli": "Paccattañca sarīresu, ",
          "en": "In individual human bodies "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.20",
          "pli": "manussesvetaṃ na vijjati; ",
          "en": "you can’t find such distinctions. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.21",
          "pli": "Vokārañca manussesu, ",
          "en": "The distinctions among humans "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:9.22",
          "pli": "samaññāya pavuccati. ",
          "en": "are spoken of by convention. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.1",
          "pli": "Yo hi koci manussesu, ",
          "en": "Anyone among humans "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.2",
          "pli": "gorakkhaṃ upajīvati; ",
          "en": "who lives off keeping cattle: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.3",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi, ",
          "en": "know them, Vāseṭṭha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.4",
          "pli": "kassako so na brāhmaṇo. ",
          "en": "as a farmer, not a brahmin. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.5",
          "pli": "Yo hi koci manussesu, ",
          "en": "Anyone among humans "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.6",
          "pli": "puthusippena jīvati; ",
          "en": "who lives off various professions: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.7",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi, ",
          "en": "know them, Vāseṭṭha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "mn98:10.8",
          "pli": "sippiko so na brāhmaṇo. ",
          "en": "as a professional, not a brahmin. "
